[1] Date: Thu 5 Jun 2008
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2008; 21(23) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Highly pathogenic avian influenza, United Kingdom
-------------------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 5 Jun 2008 from Dr Nigel Gibbens,
chief veterinary officer, Department for Environment, Food and Rural
Affairs (Defra), London, United Kingdom.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 22 May 2008
Date of first confirmation of the event: 4 Jun 2008
Report date: 5 Jun 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 5 Jun 2008

Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus, serotype H7N7
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Shenington, Oxfordshire, England
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 May 2008
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: birds
Susceptible: 25 000
Cases: 15 000
Deaths: 10 000
Destroyed: 15 000
Slaughtered: --
Affected population: laying flock of _Gallus gallus_ [chickens].

Outbreak statistics
Species: birds
Apparent morbidity rate: 60 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 40 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 66.67 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter
** not_calc_miss_info

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.

Epidemiological comments: first noted 2 weeks ago with mild clinical
disease. Marked clinical disease in 2 sheds was then observed on 31
May 2008. Epidemiological investigation is in progress.
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: VLA Weybridge (OIE's reference laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT)
Test date: 5 Jun 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: neuraminidase inhibition assay
Test date: 5 Jun 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: real-time PCR (polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 5 Jun 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: virus isolation
Test date: 5 Jun 2008
Result: positive

Species: birds
Test: virus sequencing
Test date: 5 Jun 2008
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

